WEBVTT

00:00:02.730 --> 00:00:05.100
DAN GILBERT: Its a
desire we all share.

00:00:05.100 --> 00:00:08.930
"To lead a rich,
fulfilling, happy life."

00:00:08.930 --> 00:00:11.260
But you cant always
get what you want.

00:00:11.260 --> 00:00:13.930
ELIZABETH GILBERT: Why are we so
fickle? Why is it that one day

00:00:13.930 --> 00:00:16.800
the things that make us happy
the next day bring us misery?

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:20.330
DAN GILBERT: This emotional
life is a roller coaster...

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:22.760
taking us from the
heights of ecstasy

00:00:22.760 --> 00:00:25.000
to the depths of despair
and every place between.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:26.660
KATIE COURIC: All
emotions have a role

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:29.160
in a healthy life;
were not automatons.

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:32.000
"Im Dan Gilbert,
and in this series,"

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:33.400
Im going to introduce you

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:35.600
"to everyday people who are
searching for happiness,"

00:00:35.600 --> 00:00:37.930
as well as to the scientists

00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:41.160
and clinicians who are
trying to help them find it.

00:00:41.160 --> 00:00:42.460
BARBARA ROTHBAUM:
What Ive taken away

00:00:42.460 --> 00:00:44.560
is the resilience
of the human spirit.

00:00:44.560 --> 00:00:49.960
It is just amazing what we
can go through and be okay.

00:00:49.960 --> 00:00:52.730
WARREN KING: At first I
thought I was going crazy--

00:00:52.730 --> 00:00:56.660
"the dreams, the nightmares--
but Im not letting it beat me."

00:00:56.660 --> 00:00:58.530
What more can I say?

00:00:58.530 --> 00:01:01.160
Im a happy camper.

00:01:01.160 --> 00:01:03.230
GILBERT: Well see how our
greatest source of happiness

00:01:03.230 --> 00:01:05.730
lies in the people around us.

00:01:05.730 --> 00:01:08.330
SETH POLLAK: The lesson weve
learned is that a basic need

00:01:08.330 --> 00:01:12.160
"for human beings is
love, is companionship."

00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:14.230
GILBERT: Well see
what happiness is...

00:01:14.230 --> 00:01:15.400
what causes it...

00:01:15.400 --> 00:01:18.530
and why we look for it
in all the wrong places.

00:01:18.530 --> 00:01:20.900
WOMAN: I used to think that
things would make me happy.

00:01:20.900 --> 00:01:22.460
"Or money, success."

00:01:22.460 --> 00:01:24.500
Im realizing now that
thats not the fact.

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:26.260
Happiness comes from within.

00:01:26.260 --> 00:01:29.660
"GILBERT: But next, well explore
the obstacles to happiness."

00:01:29.660 --> 00:01:32.600
"Emotions such as fear,
sadness and anger."

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:34.000
JOHN McENROE: Have I lost it

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:37.100
to the point where I did
feel like Ive lost it? Yeah.

00:01:37.100 --> 00:01:40.630
I went through like six or
seven years of real depression.

00:01:40.630 --> 00:01:42.660
I just was never quite
given the right pill.

00:01:42.660 --> 00:01:45.560
"GILBERT: Asking why we have
them, why we need them"

00:01:45.560 --> 00:01:48.230
and how we can all keep
them under control.

00:01:48.230 --> 00:01:50.060
"WOMAN: I remember
Caitlin screaming,"

00:01:50.060 --> 00:01:52.230
"""You dont understand
how horrible it is to be"

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:54.900
"""caught in this
brain that doesnt work"

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:56.660
"and I want you to fix this."""

